I did not get the idea behind the game. Divorced parents - okay. Father's troubled childhood - okay. These themes are not shocking nowadays. The ending doesn't explain why the person needed to remember the past
Extremely buggy, on landscape the dioramas are too small to see and on portrait, inventory items can't be used. The swiping controls are also buggy.
Story was amazing, could've expanded a bit more on ending but easy puzzles and good walk through when I was stuck
Out of this world üåé üò™ ‚ù§ ü§ß ‚ú® üòç
I played this game through and through and I LOVE IT! The art is amazing, the story is compelling, even the soundtrack is great! I recommend this to anyone who loves games like this!

I really enjoyed this mini-room game! I couldn't adapt to the default swiping controls, but the game lets you change that in the settings. The difficulty level was just right. Some of the puzzles, like the "mail chute" system, were very clever. The game has an unsettling quality and eerie atmosphere. Like many others here, I just wish the final chapter had more substance. Why ask for a review on the last screen, before the player even has a chance to realize the game is over?!
A nice simple puzzle game, not too difficult.

Good adventure. Graphics (colours) hard to see on my tablet .... but ok on larger screen. Good puzzles to solve (had to refer to a walkthrough in some places) . Moving from panel to panel sometimes awkward .... have to make sure you are dragging in the right place. Easy to get lost .... but that adds to the mystery of the game. Enjoyed playing it .... thanks!
This game was very intriguing from start to finish. Very nice graphics. Easy to navigate and understand. 9/10 just because there isn't 500 more levels lol

A terrific experience and a truly meaningful, enjoyable game. Puzzles were calibrated optimally for my cranium which prevents headaches and speaking through clenched teeth. I'll definitely be watching for a sequel. Thank you for several very enjoyable hours on my tablet!
Hard To see gameplay
Creepy and pretty to look at

Interesting story. Good puzzles. A bit short. Felt cheated in the end. You game is spent with the idea that you are working to get to the woods/campgrounds and the tree house, so you'd think it would be the longest level, or at least a full level. The woods/campgrounds was a short cut scene, and the tree house was only 5 squares. Very disappointing ending.
Awesome
Graphic are great but it could have been longer. Unless there is a part 2!
Short but fun
The storyline is pretty good and the gameplay is simple enough to please most
Amazing game! Easy puzzles but its interesting, I would recommend anyone that wants to play it.
The game carries an interesting concept.
I love weather factory and this is another ace game!

The game play and art are great. The only downfall I found is that the meaning of the storyline isn't clear cut by the end. I had to search externally to find some discussion of the overarching plot and minutiae to have it all make sense.

Well... I loved the puzzles, the setting. But the end is so... Crude. I wish it could have a more precise closure, some kind of explanation tying all together (although this could be on purpose). Anyways, a nice game. Kinda eerie. Be warned haha
Beautifully made eerie puzzle game.
Out standing, and thrilling game amazing story and level building
It was a good game but the story was a little bit confusing... Not sure what happened... Did the father do something to her or the mother? It's just a bit unclear.

"Oh hey, this is like that 'Tiny Room' game. That was cool, i'll check this out." No no. This thing emotionally wrecked me. It's super cute, but then punches you in the face with great puzzles & a plot that legit made me question my existence & even tear up. I think it could be longer & more in depth but I genuinely loved the 2 hours or so that I played it. Short, sweet, to the point, & an emotional roller coaster. Just the way I likes my games.
Mostly logical and attention to detail is all you need
it's hard to interact with story points like with the key in the beginning, it doesn't let me drag it to the door and it chooses something else instead
Amazing game, albeit short. Definitely give it a shot.
Beautiful game

It could be a decent game, but it feels like something is missing, especially final chapter looks so incomplete. I didn't even realized I finished the game when suddenly titles appeared out of nowhere :)
Love the premise and the story however differentiating objects is challenging. The controls are obtuse and art style is okay. This is on Android.

The art design was terrific. I wanted to explore more of this world, but you have a very linear path. I enjoyed the story and found the narrative style refreshing and engaging, but the final chapter felt like it was very rushed. Ultimately, this is worth the purchase and is an enjoyable few hours, but a little incomplete narratively.
Fantastic
Uninstalled after 20 minutes, controls are too aggravating.
Love the game but it left me wanting more
i love how its in plain sight like wow!
Beautiful ‚Äúescape the room‚Äù like. Yet i don't feel compelled to play further than the first few rooms.
Unplayable on Xiomi9S
Art is great, but the control is so so. Also the story doesn't seem to have a proper ending.
Greeat game. Love the gameplay, would be better if it's longer!
Doesn't support 21:9.

I can see that this was well thought out, but it's almost impossible to play as the some of the actions you have to do are in the same exact spot as the map and option buttons. And if you switch to landscape view, your inventory is all jacked up. So close, yet so far away.

A cryptic story, at times unsettling, contained within dioramas that are beautifully crafted yet bland to play in. The puzzles and story are a disjointed, confusing mess that don't have the impact they should. Often had to resort to a guide, and it's bad the guide is video only. The controls are terrible, and navigating between rooms is an awful and time consuming process. It's totally unclear what is interactive, so you end up having to tap on everything you see indiscriminately. A flawed game.

This game was an experience. The puzzles are well laid out and the story was compelling. Ending is a bit unclear, but I think that's the point. There's enough clues about the plot throughout the game that you can definitely come to your own conclusion as you reflect on it after (and you will). All in all, 2.5 hours well spent.
Okay game but the ending lacked the punch and gravitas that it seemed to need.

I really like the gameplay. Especially with the intricacy of the puzzles. At the same time, I wish there were more details and explanations as to what happened to the main character. There's a lot left to be desired.
The only challenge is to find the objects, puzzles are straightforward. Scenes are not zoomable. Story somewhat interesting, dark and you can relate.

The story is interesting and the puzzles keep your brain working. However, it doesn't seem very optimized for tablets. In portrait mode the top of the screen is nearly inaccessible due to the menu buttons and in landscape mode the inventory is inaccessible because the items duplicate and stretch so that they cannot be selected.

Neat looking, that's about it. The writing is super dramatic. The protagonist pretty much screams "I AM A VICTIM!" every time I found a clue. I spent a lot of time just poking at every item on the screen until something happened. Boring. Wish I could get a refund.
Such an aesthetically pleasing game and a fun escape room complex that kept me occupied for a while, just wish it was longer
It's literally unplayable on a Galaxy Note 8. I want to play this. It seems like a game I would really enjoy. I probably get 5fps and it messes with the controls.

rooms were entirely too small and far away to even see any detail. when you click on items they were so blown up on the screen I could barely read the letter that says the treehouse is safe. and I dont have a cheap phone in the slightest have never had an issue with a game till now
Unique gameplay unveiling a dark story as you play.
Solid story and riddles, lovely art
I liked the overall vibe, but felt that the ending was too abrupt. I really enjoyed it though.
Low-key spookiness and low-key puzzles, cool art.
It was ok, the puzzles were somewhat challenging though very dull, would get bored to easily.

The Almost Gone is probably the most detailed and visually attractive isometric puzzle games I've played recently - so if you're into the thrill of exploring tiny environments - give this game a shot. The story however, leaves a lot to be desired - a dreamy (occasionally creepy) mystery that in the end feels like it wrote too many checks it can't cash. My main criticism is how cliched and tiresome the dialogue got by the 2nd chapter 'We get it. Your childhood messed you up - enough already.'

For those unaware, you can change the controls in the settings, so you dont have to swipe to change rooms, that really made the experience better for me. The story is interesting, but the ending leaves it open to interpretation. So you never really get an explanation as to what happened. Just clues that lead the player to a certain, vague conclusion. 1st playthrough was good but 2nd playthrough was less the 30 mins. 0 replayability. I liked it but wouldnt pay for it, but I'd play a part 2.

This was odd, because the structure of the game is very intriguing, and the puzzles are very clever. But I just didn't get the flow of the story. Did I miss something? Is there an odd disconnect in the translation?
It's cool but I keep getting stuck
The door on the globe won't open. Shame, I was enjoying the game
A deep, dark experience that will haunt your mind. Incredible.
Beautiful graphics
Very good game! I have a problem though. SPOILER I went again to r. 510 in chapter 4 and cant go back since elevator doesnt work. How to go back?
Ephemeral.
Marvelously fun and addictive.

I absolutely LOVED this game, yes the ending had me disappointed but only because I wanted more and I hope the ending was intended to keep us rooting for almost gone 2 if there will be one. I'd definitely pay for another game just like this. Hands down one of my favorite puzzle games in forever! Thank you üòÅüòÅüëèüèªüëçüèª
Dark but really enjoyable game. I didnt have any issues or glitches throughout, graphics were very clear. Abrupt ending so don't anticipate a resolution if you are hoping for one.
Beautiful, and dark.
Great game, but the mobile controls for moving from room to room were a bit frustrating.

The puzzles are cohesive and the story is really great- I really loved this game but gave it 4 instead of 5 because I don't really feel the price of the game necessarily reflects the length all that well. It's pretty short. As a lover of these kinds of story driven puzzle games though I feel it was still worth it. I'd probably give it a 4.5 if I could.

Starts off intriguing and mysterious but ends up being frustrating with poor controls and a story that abruptly ends without providing any closure. For better or worse none of the puzzles were overly complex and it only took a few hours to complete. Glad it was free with Google Play Pass.

The atmosphere and narrative for this game is dark and interesting, and the puzzles are hard without being frustrating. However, the controls are truly awful, often leaving one annoyed (spinning rooms by error, etc). A brief tutorial for controls at the start of the game would be really useful. This is a decent effort but doesn't quite hit the mark.

Great game, love the art style and some nice puzzles. The controls for orbiting the scene can some times be a little finicky, but overall that's excusable for some a nicely designed and thought out game.

It caught me right from the beginning. Before I realized it, I was spending all of my spare time playing it. The puzzles were great to solve, and the graphics are great. Very well put together. Only 4 stars though, as I think the story could have been a little more explained throughout the game. Also the ending feels a little unfinished, like maybe it's not really the end. All in all, it's fun and I really recommend it.

The game is well made and visually appealing, the puzzles are good, I just don't think this game style is appropriate for this kind of story. I've played the Silent Age and Tiny Room but discovering the truly messed up nature of this story through moving a book is just horrific

The simple art style of the game is sharp and pleasing, and the concept of this kind of puzzle story definitely has merit, but the execution fell short in the end. The controls are pretty bad, sometimes you try to swipe to move to a different section and it rotates instead, other times it's vice versa. The story leaves much to be desired, especially considering how it's teased in the description. The end is unsatisfactory, there was build up for naught. I wanted to like this game, I really did.
Cool puzzles, lovely presentation and a fairly interesting overarching plot tying things together. I did occasionally find navigation frustrating.
Finished game. Was a great game. Depressing but otherwise good. Thanks for allowing me to finish.
Well done dark puzzle game. Not super long, not too difficult, but we'll designed and entertaining!
The story ultimately did resonate. It takes a while to get rolling though. The controls can be frustrating at times.
Beautiful little puzzle game, but the payoff to the story is rushed and leaves you unsatisfied

This game was honestly the best game I have ever played! It has a very easy to follow story and a lovable character. A mysterious puzzle game that teases the mind and also shows inside the mind of a small child. So good, and worth spending the money! ‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§
Cant move from room to room without wanting to scream keeps spinning instead I'm done too frustrating

The Almost Gone is a solid puzzle adventure game with a moody atmosphere built on minimal storytelling and exploration that keeps you interested to continue onwards throughout the game. Unfortunately not counting achievements, once your done there's no real reason to play this ever again unless you really like it, but regardless this was a solid experience worth checking out at a reasonable length and challenge!

Overall it has an amazing design and a very interesting dark mood. The puzzle is fairly simple, but fun to play. The end is what ruins it, there is a moment that the game ends but the mystery is not solved. It just ends there and that's it. An issue with the plot, all the rest is pretty cool!
Kind of hard but fun
Confusing

A good case of style over substance, really. Fantastic art design and a story that leaves an unsatisfactory taste in the mouth. By no means difficult but enjoyable to play, I was genuinely surprised when the game ended. The ending felt unfinished rather than open and for that gives the impression that the game is shorter than it actually is. Interested to see what the developer does in the future!
Beautiful art style with smooth controls and interesting puzzles

This game is awful. The controls are buggy and so difficult to use. I am constantly moving when I don't want to and on one of the puzzles there was no way to input the solution properly. Also the puzzles are vague and with no real map it's impossible to tell where you have been or where to go next. Also very difficult to know what you can zoom in on and what's just decoration. Good atmosphere but only gave me headaches. Horrible.

It took me a minute to get in to it, and it was a bit confusing to figure out, but once you get the creators train of thought, it's not so bad. The navigation controls are garbage and the story line isn't well written, it's very vague, even in the end, you finish the game feeling cheated. The colors are bland, but it is beautifully done. I was definitely hoping for more, though.
Looks good but the navigation is so awful that I just couldn't keep playing past the first few rooms.
Pretty, but the touchscreen controls are awful.

This was a great game. It took me back to playing Myst with my parents back in the 90s, a game I felt was very spooky, mysterious, and a little scary. The ethereal slow pace of Almost Gone make it very peaceful to play, though the subject matter is quite dark.
Even though it's a sad subject, it felt so relaxing to play.

Clever and well made narrative puzzle game. There is lots of variety of problems to solve. Not too easy or hard. Minor downsides are the finicky controls and getting stuck because you missed a very small spot to tap on.

I REALLY wanted to like it.. but i had to cheat on the first level. The controls are SO TERRIBLE it ruins the game play to a point that ur ready to throw the phone! THIS GAME IS NOT RELAXING BECAUSE OF THAT VERT REASON.. it cant tell the difference between turning and swiping, no matter how slow and careful u do it. It just makes for a VERY frustrating game exp.. on chapter 2 now.. uninstalling. I CANT EVEN.
Very great gameplay

Enjoyed the puzzles. Doesn't require using a walkthrough. Great story. Although somehow I must have missed how the narrator died and what happened to the narrator's parents....will probably play again and figure out what I missed. Took about 7 hours to complete.
"this game was great" - - my 4 year old. It is a story game about a troubled family explored through some narration and finding memories of his past. Pretty cleverly told and somewhat disturbing.
Great game with nice puzzles, controls can be a bit tedious sometimes. Played as part of the play pass, think I would have enjoyed less if I paid full price.

This was... incredibly beautiful, but also so so lackluster. So many questions go unanswered, like the dresser in the house or why the characters acted one way or the other. I felt there was something that I was not seeing, that was not being told, and it was frustrating. As for the gameplay... It can be very "click everything until something works", and changing scenes is absolutely awful. 60% of times the rooms did the opposite of what I wanted. I liked this game, but I expected more.
A fun let down I love these kind of games but the navigation was difficult and there was no "ending" to the story. Amazing graphics and game play though.

Terrible ending. Leaves you hanging and depressed for them all. The definition of a game is striving toward a goal or ending. All progress in this game only is toward a spiralling downward crash. There is no ending in this game, only a sudden stop.
This game makes you use your brain. I love it

Unique. I spend so much time trying to find cool, unique adventure/hidden object games but most of them are all alike. This is one of the best. Rusty lake & Forgotten Hill were my favorites but this may be better! Hope to see more from this developer, soon.

I saw this long ago on steam and played the demo on there, liking what I saw. When it popped up again on the play pass it made me really happy. Especially since it has a hefty price on steam. The story is touchy, not for everyone as it can be pretty heavy and hit too close to home for some people. But the story telling mechanic is nice. Some puzzles are confusing, but there are walkthroughs online.
Absolutely amazing gameplay but an overall disappointing ending, would be much better if it had a longer storyline.
I don't really know what this game about
Absolutely stunning game beautiful and entertaining. It can be difficult in some sections but try to approach things logically. If you get stuck there's an excellent walkthrough on YouTube
Fun and enjoyable
Cute while free. Chapter 5 is nothing but an ending. If I had paid, I think I would have felt unsatisfied. Since it was free, it was a fun experience while it lasted.
This game sucks and very hard to understand.
It good
Amazing story! It has me at the edge of my seat whenever I figure things out
BEAUTIFUL GRAPHICS BAR NONE
It was okay... Not my type of game..

Very Fun and Puzzling Game! The game itself has such a simple design but it just captures everything! The controls are a tad bit weird but I got the hand of it after the first couple of rooms. The story was good not the best but still none the less a good story. The puzzles were tough at times but nothing for a person who plays puzzle games all the time. The game isn't super long and it's long enough that I can say it is well worth the 7$.
It was good but the ending leaves nothing. Maybe a cliffhanger for another part?

I feel more confused than I was when I started playing. I didn't get WHY, HOW, or even really WHAT actually happened. Was it Mom? Or was it Dad? Or was it self? I'm so lost. I wish it would have been clearer at the end. I feel like the game was kind of pointless... Please update the end to at least have script explaining what actually happened?

The game is subtle and haunting, but while the ending was clearly trying to make you read between the lines it instead just falls flat - a mild disappointment after the quality of the game leading up to it. If you like puzzle games, it's well worth playing.
Great game, just the right amount of difficulty but not too hard. Interesting story line.

Spoiler ahead- EDIT: Once I updated the game, it worked. The developers responded promptly and offered a refund but I declined since the update worked. The game is intriguing, the concept is interesting, but the controls are tough. I can never get the rooms to swipe. This does not work for me. content: Good puzzler.
I just couldnt get into it.

The game is really well designed, both the visuals and the sound are great with a unique style. The playthrough was really short and felt like half a story. You get teased with mystery without any payoff of a reveal. Other games in the genre offer a fuller experience, something you can really get your teeth into. Sadly, this pales in comparison and feels very shallow.
Meh, a beautiful game with a great story completely shattered by absolutely horrid controls, short gameplay, and a subpar ost. Pass this one, and watch an LP of it instead, save your money.

Nice distraction. The puzzles were not too hard. The story line was vague and confusing. The ending was lame. The controls were hard to manage. But it kept me engaged for a few hours. I was able to solve it without using the walkthrough.
Fun game to go through. You'll probably get around 3-4 hours if you take your time.
A lot of bugs and crashes... this game was released prematurely

content: Intersting game but short
I struggled alittle but that makes it more fun
Great game but it was easy to get stuck the clues are cryptic but great game.

Absolutely mesmerizing. The stunning graphics and eerie sounds go perfectly well together and give the story a very creepy yet beautiful feel to it that I was not expecting. It is a very stunning game but i felt that it gave me more questions than answers. The story itself is decent but a bit messy and could have had a better execution. Over all was a fun game to plag only wished they went futher in depth in some things. Hopefully they make a squeal.

The underlying story feels extremely simple and vague, doesn't evolve much over the course of the game, and the ending (if you could even call it that) didn't really answer any questions or wrap the game up in any way. *WAY* too much work was wasted on unnecessarily detailed environments, and no work went into the story, which is why (in my opinion) nothing that this game was going for was actually achieved. This is less of a game, and more of a shallow, pretentious showpiece.
I almost
Awesome game!
It was a good game but I thought the goal was to find out how you died

This was a great game, however for some reason I didn't get the achievement for finishing it the first time. I now have all the others, but there's no way to get the first one. It should be awarded retroactively if you've already finished the game.

Very enjoyable game and I really liked the storyline. For me the final Act was just too short and unsatisfying, I didn't feel the story was resolved well and it brought down the whole game for me really. I think the length of the game also doesn't justify the price, it should be cheaper.

I like the premise and art style but something about it doesn't make me want to play at all and I think it's the navigation. Turning and moving shouldn't both be controlled by swipes. they are not precise enough and that makes them far from disability friendly. I always turn when I want to move and move when I want to turn. It's annoying. I've seen other games with this perspective use swipes to turn and buttons to move. like in the doorways. That feels leagues better
The game looks good but the controls made me stop playing this game, it can have better and more friendly touch controls.

The game had beautiful imagery with some really lovely attention to detail in an elaborate exploration of dioramas mapping intergenerational trauma. The controls make sense, as long as I paid attention & was able to be precise, I could navigate. Still it was never intuitive for me & still regularly changing rooms when I meant to turn the room which was a little frustrating. The story was interesting and the puzzles fun but the ending didnt feel like it pulled the story together the way I hoped.

Lackluster story with some decently polished graphics will mildly entertain you for a few hours. Rather short, vague plots w/o full resolution, and some trickier controls make this game ok but not great. A few secret achievements weren't enough to make me try for them. I paid with play pass so for me the "price" was acceptable but would pass on an investment of real money. Also, may be triggering for some as game deals with dark themes including abuse, neglect, animal violence, & death.
How games should be designed.
I really liked the puzzles and atmospheric tone. Some of the controls were frustrating but over all a nice experience.
It was a great story, a little dark and cryptic, but very good. I just wish it was longer.
Super creative and mysterious

I enjoyed my brief time with this. It has a lovely style, a fairly interesting narrative and a satisfying degree of puzzling. As other folk have commented, you do feel... almost empty.. at the end. Maybe that's deliberate! Glad to have played it, though, and appreciate all the effort and love that obviously went into it.
Cute game controls could be better soetimes it swipes rooms instead of change camera angle
Another boring and worse clone of the room
The controls, moving from room to room, is annoying and doesn't always work how its meant to. But the story is nice and its a quick little game
I absolutely loved this game. It wasnt too short like other story games.
Very beautiful game with a good story. The ending was a bit abrupt and kind of a let down after all the tension and buildup that came before it.
Once i was able to get in its a really fun game and the mecanics are easy just wish there was more direction of what to do

content: Such a beautiful, thought-provoking game! Clearly the devs paid much attention to detail, and the game shows the love. Insignificant permissions (thank you, devs). Easy learning curve for controls; ingenious, sufficiently challenging puzzles; well-written, sincere story; mysterious and beautiful environment. Really enjoyed how the story reveals itself as you explore the meticulously designed dioramas. Even played it through a few times to see what I might've missed. Well worth the asking price.
Hard to move to different rooms/areas. It just spins the room instead of moving to a different room.
Fun mystery puzzle game. Would definitely recommend!

[[SPOILERS AHEAD]] PROS: Absolutely love the art style, characters and puzzle layout! The way the scenery told the story was really really cool, and the puzzles were challenging but not frustrating - perfect blend! CONS: The controls between spinning and swiping were a bit hard to get used to, and the ending felt like it just ripped out all the amazing build-up that was happening - so many great characters and perspectives that felt like they got slammed shut with no real end. Ergo, 3/5 ! :,)

content: Fantastic story and gameplay! The puzzles weren't too difficult and they were unique on their own ways. The artstyle of it was also really amazing. The story got me hooked and wondered a lot on what happened altho I expected more for the ending, but as a nice puzzle game this was worth to try. I still really liked the little horror aspects from it!
Great graphics, lame gameplay
I love the graphics and the puzzles weren't too hard either! The story was very interesting and I'd definitely recommend this game. I wish there was more to play I enjoyed it too much!
Definitely a somewhat challenging puzzle game but it does feel a little short...

It's alright, i guess. The graphics are gorgeous. However, moving around is troublesome (often i tried swiping to move to the next section but it kept misreading as spinning the room; i did find a way but it was pretty annoying for a while.) The last chapter felt...underwhelming?

Maybe I'm playing this on the wrong device (a phone), but the clues are really hard to see and movement is nearly impossible. I can't figure out the difference between moving between rooms and spinning the room around. Tried playing four times, but just annoying.
replyContent: Thank you for the feedback. We are working on a solution to make clues more visible. to help get your bearings: Swipe under the diorama to rotate it. Tap on the diorama and swipe on the diorama to move from one to the other. At the bottom in between the two circular buttons there is a minmap to see what directions you can go. Hope that helps :)

content: Slow start and not a lot of hand holding to get you going, but it was a a great game that really made you think. Puzzles are great. We'll worth the cost of admission.
Very hard control :(

content: This game is amazing in basically every way. It is relaxing and not too hard but hard enough that you cant breeze through it. Its very well done for a mobile game from the music to graphics to gameplay. The only downside to it is that the story doesnt make much sense with the death aspect. Through the whole game they never mention her dying and you never uncovered how she died either. The ending in my opinion was a complete bust and felt very left open. Otherwise 10/10 worth the purchase.
The game has beautiful aesthetics! Amazing art and great attention to details. It tells a compelling and a very human story. Absloutly love it!
Won't load. Spent a relatively large sum of money for the app and I can't get it to work on my Samsung S10+. Ridiculous.

Seriously addictive!
fun puzzle game with nice graphics and a good art style

content: Good game, I'm enjoying the puzzles but the swipe to move between areas is incredibly frustrating, especially as the same move rotates the view. Please make it arrows instead!

Well, that was a trip. I honestly have no words to describe this. I am reminded of the game Gone Home. The premise of that was similar in a couple ways. That being said, while I didn't like Gone Home, this one was alright. The game play wasn't overly complicated, and I only went to the walk-through once before realizing I already knew the answer. The story revolves around Emily, who, I believe, has returned after a while away, only to be locked in her room. Escape. Discover. Solve puzzles.

Alright I bought this because I was bored, it's overall okay, the puzzles were fun, but I feel the story was too short, easy to miss out on details, the sound was good but the loop was not, it was clearly noticable when the music stopped and started again, so that's a down side. The story was well written but I wished that I had more of it. Well designed puzzles. I love these types of puzzle games but because I had to pay for this game I wish it was longer.
Such a great story and love the gameplay!!! Really sad but lasting impression!!! Please make another!!!
This game was really good. It was unsettling and insightful. The controls for navigation are a bit frustrating though. Overall, it was a great mobile experience. I highly recommend it.

*sigh* This, overall, was an excellent game. It has aesthetic graphics, is fun to play, and only takes you about 5 hours to complete. However, it has the most unsatisfying ending of ALL TIME. Circle endings can be good (I should know‚Äî I'm an author!), but this game absolutely failed it. Play it for the spatial reasoning and memory practice, but only if you like it for the game itself and not the storyline or plot. It was good overall, but I wouldn't recommend this to others.

At the bottom in between the two circular buttons there is a minmap to see what directions you can go. Hope that helps.

content: I love a good puzzle box game, this one doesn't disappoint in that regard. It's beautiful, the music is the right balance between soothing and creepy, and the puzzles are and engaging and challenging without being frustrating. I thoroughly enjoyed the playthrough, but the story is lacking and left me disappointed and unfulfilled at the end. It's ambiguous -- you only sorta-kinda find out what happened. It left me with a general "I guess.." feeling, and not at all like all of my work paid off.

The puzzles were hard to the right extent, but the game was really short; I expected more content. The control were very counter-intuitive with the two different swipes, and the position of the "X" button as well. The storyline was deep and vaguely interesting, but it led nowhere at the end of the game. I'll rate it higher if the game gets extended.

The developer was quick to respond with a work-around for an issue I was having getting the game started. I believe any developer that does that with an actually working work-around deserves a 5 star rating, in my opinion! Thanks guys!
replyContent: Hello, We're investigating the issue, seems to be cloud save related. We're doing our best to fix it asap. There's a workaround, please, disconnect from google play services from main menu before starting the game. We're working on a fix in the meantime but you should be able to play.

content: Just finished the first part and I've to say, it's amazing! The story, the subtle clues as to what is going on, the graphics, all end up creating an immensely realistic experience. Will update my review after I finish the game!
I've been waiting for this game to come out and I bought it the second it was available. Beautiful graphics and puzzles that can be tricky but not impossible, this game is well worth the purchase.

Beautiful, thoughtful, and incredibly moving. Controls for moving and turning the rooms were a bit wonky; sometimes a room would turn when I didn't mean for it to, or I'd move to a room I didn't mean to. But overall it was incredible to follow Emily's journey. I kinda wish I knew what had happened to her, but the downfall of her parents marriage and her mother's mental health was terribly sad. Lovely game, thank you.
Runs extremely slow in S8.

The game is simple and probably only worth playing on mobile. As for the narrative, I get what they are trying to tell, but it's very easy to miss some details. Overall the experience was mediocre. It's got very good aesthetics, but overall too short.
Trippy, and well written. This game is as beautiful as it is simple. Though I wish I learned even more from the story. It feels like it will have interesting things to find on a second playthrough.
This game is worth every penny. Beautiful interface, engaging story, not frustratingly challenging, and I want to play it over again.

So far, the story has me intrigued, and hooked. Beautifully done. The puzzles are challenging, but the game is worth the challenge. The story seems to nudge you to figure out what happened. So, awesome game.
